in paid products, or using the Software to provide revenue-generating services.

"Model Artifacts" means model weights, checkpoints, tokenizers, adapters,
datasets, prompts, or other AI assets that are distributed by third parties and
used with or alongside the Software.

"Platform-Required Rights" means the limited rights required by a repository
hosting platform (for example GitHub) to host, copy, index, display, and enable
standard collaboration workflows such as forks, pull requests, and code review.

